  "rationale": "<p>Choice D is correct. For a linear equation in a form <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"a, x plus b, equals, c x plus d\"></span> to have no solutions, the <span class=\"italic\">x</span>-terms must have equal coefficients and the remaining terms must not be equal. Expanding the right-hand side of the given equation yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"9 x plus 5, equals, a, x plus a, b\"></span>. Inspecting the <span class=\"italic\">x</span>-terms, 9 must equal <span class=\"italic\">a, </span>so statement I must be true. Inspecting the remaining terms, 5 can&rsquo;t equal <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"9 b\"></span><span class=\"italic\">. </span>Dividing both of these quantities by 9 yields that <span class=\"italic\">b</span> can&rsquo;t equal <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"five ninths\"></span>. Therefore, statement III must be true. Since <span class=\"italic\">b</span> can have any value other than <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"five ninths\"></span>, statement II may or may not be true.<p>Choice A is incorrect. For the given equation to have no solution, both <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"a, equals 9 \"></span> and <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"b is not equal to five ninths \"></span> must be true. Choice B is incorrect because it must also be true that <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"b is not equal to five ninths \"></span>. Choice C is incorrect because when <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"a, equals 9 \"></span>, there are many values of <span class=\"italic\">b </span>that lead to an equation having no solution. That is, <span class=\"italic\">b</span> might be 5, but <span class=\"italic\">b</span> isn&rsquo;t required to be 5.</p></p>\n",
